    "It is an extension of the selfattention mechanism, allowing the model to compute multiple self-attention modules simultaneously in different representation subspaces.",
    "The main idea is to map the input sequence into multiple representation spaces, compute self-attention in each, and then combine the results.The advantage of the multi-head self-attention mechanism lies in its ability to capture complex dependencies between different positions in the input sequence and semantic information in different representation spaces.",
    "By computing multiple heads in parallel, significant speed-up in computation can be achieved, enhancing the model's learning efficiency.",
    "Therefore, the multi-head self-attention mechanism has shown promising results in various sequence modeling tasks, such as language modeling, machine translation, and text classification.",
